# Documentation Structure

The root `README.md` is the **single source of truth** for all shared project documentation:
- Features, CAN tables, OBD polling tables, architecture diagram, roadmap, hardware, settings, brand

**`android/README.md`** is build/dev only:
- Build instructions, project structure, development guide (adding CAN signals/PIDs), doc links
- Links to root README for everything else — never duplicate CAN tables, features, or roadmap here

**`firmware/README.md`** is firmware-specific only:
- Build instructions, REST API, BLE GATT, NVS keys, drive mode CAN frames, directory structure
- Links to root README for the project-wide roadmap

## When updating shared content

- CAN frame IDs, OBD polling intervals, formulas → update root `README.md` and `android/docs/pid-reference.md`
- Roadmap changes → update root `README.md` only
- Feature additions/removals → update root `README.md` and browser emulator
- Never copy shared tables or sections into `android/README.md` or `firmware/README.md`
